description:
# Why

bl-16e9 unified the state-leg presence gate to ask `state_worktree_dir()` instead of `store.root` (so master_url mode actually pushes). That dropped the bl-88c7 "when `state_remote` is unset/==origin, `state_present` reuses `code_present` (no extra git invocation)" reuse-optimization — there is no longer a `state_remote == remote` branch.

The function-doc comment at the top of `sync_with_remote` in src/commands/sync.rs still describes the old reuse-and-byte-identical story:

    // Splitting the gates fixes that without disturbing the common case:
    // when `state_remote` is unset/==origin it resolves to the code remote,
    // `state_present` reuses `code_present` (no extra git invocation),
    // and the whole sequence is byte-identical to before this change.

A reader chasing the bl-88c7 history will find the claim no longer matches the code. The behavior comment I added below it (the bl-16e9 paragraph) supersedes it, but the two read inconsistently together.

# Concrete fix

Collapse the bl-88c7 paragraph to a one-liner that just records the split-gate motivation ("the main-branch and state-branch presence gates are independent — pre-bl-88c7 a single code-remote gate fronted both, so a hub-linked client with a reachable hub but no code origin silently skipped balls/tasks"), and let the bl-16e9 paragraph below it explain the current gate's target. No behavior change.

# Scope

- src/commands/sync.rs only
- pure comment edit; no test changes expected
